column8:
ABANDONED - DO NOT BUY

1. Start an early access campaign that relies heavily on the goodwill generated by long-past titles;
2. Lazily update;
3. Put out a dev post that states that updates are going to improve;
4. Run a 50% Steam sale to judge further interest;
5. Dump unfinished, incomplete game as a "1.0", state modders can take it from there when sale evidently doesn't make you enough cash;
6. Prove your studio is an undirected ship running onto rocks, dump all over the EA model, ensure that I will never buy a DF game again.
7. DO NOT PROFIT!!!

edit: And now 1.0 is released.  Guess what?  It's still basically a tech demo in terms of content, and is still buggy as all get-out.  You ripped off a lot of people, Double Fine.

So you like games that do what SB-DF9 couldn't be bothered to do?  If you don't mind older graphics, you will likely enjoy:

- StarTopia: very similar in scope to DF9, but miles better
- Space Colony HD: leans more toward "The Sims" in peep interaction, but still a worthy effort

You can buy both of these cheap over at www.gog.com.  Let DF-9 sink into the oblivion it deserves.  Hopefully DoubleFine will meet the same fate.

